# Packet Analyzer policy rules
#
# Keep one rule per line. Lines beginning with # are comments.
#
# block-host HOST
#   Blocks HOST and all subdomains. Example: google.com blocks www.google.com,
#   but does not block fakegoogle.com.
#
# block-ip SERVER_IP
#   Blocks traffic going to one exact destination/server IP.
#
# block-client CLIENT_IP
#   Blocks all detected traffic from one client/subscriber IP.
#
# throttle-client CLIENT_IP RATE_KBPS
#   Marks one client/subscriber IP as slowed to RATE_KBPS.
#
# quota-client CLIENT_IP BYTES RATE_KBPS
#   Slows one client/subscriber after BYTES of accounted traffic.
#
# quota-all BYTES RATE_KBPS
#   Slows every client/subscriber after BYTES of accounted traffic.

# Demo rules you can edit for interviews:
block-host neverssl.com
block-ip 148.51.155.48
block-host youtube.com
block-host instagram.com
block-ip 8.8.8.8
block-client 192.168.1.10
throttle-client 192.168.1.20 128
# throttle-client 10.177.124.95 128
# block-client 10.177.124.95
# quota-client 10.177.124.95 1048576 128
